.TH PM 1 "July 2026" "pm v0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pm \- personal package manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pm
[\fB\-h\fR] [\fB\-v\fR]
[\fBi\fR|\fBinit\fR]
[\fBt\fR|\fBthreads\fR \fITHREADS\fR]
[\fBl\fR|\fBlist\fR]
[\fBs\fR|\fBsystem\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pm
is a package manager that reads a Lua configuration file and
coordinates the download, build, and installation of software packages
from remote URLs. Packages are processed in parallel using POSIX
threads.
.PP
On each run
.B pm
reads
.IR ~/.config/pm/init.lua .
For each package defined in the configuration it checks whether a newer
version is available on the remote server. If the remote file has been
modified since the last download, the tarball or source is fetched,
extracted, built with the provided shell script, and the resulting
artifact is copied into the binary directory.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Display version, copyright, and license information, then exit.
.TP
\fBi\fR, \fBinit\fR
Create a template configuration file at
.IR ~/.config/pm/init.lua
and process it. The template includes a bootstrap package that
reinstalls
.B pm
itself from GitHub.
.TP
\fBt\fR, \fBthreads\fR \fITHREADS\fR
Use at most
.I THREADS
parallel threads when building packages. If not specified, the number
of online CPU cores is used.
.TP
\fBl\fR, \fBlist\fR
List all packages along with their origin URL. They don't have to be installed.
.TP
\fBs\fR, \fBsystem\fR
Print the current system configuration: config file path, build cache
directory, binary directory, package count, and thread count.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is a Lua script located at
.IR ~/.config/pm/init.lua .
It must define the following global tables:
.TP
.B Build
A table with a single field:
.RS
.TP
.B path
Directory for downloaded sources and build caches.
Default:
.IR ~/.local/share/pm/cache/ .
.RE
.TP
.B Bin
A table with a single field:
.RS
.TP
.B path
Directory where built executables are installed.
Default:
.IR ~/.local/share/pm/bin/ .
.RE
.TP
.B Packages
An array of package tables. Each package may contain:
.RS
.TP
.B url
(Required) URL of the source archive to download.
.TP
.B name
(Optional) File name for the downloaded source. If omitted the
filename is extracted from the URL.
.TP
.B build
(Required) Shell command or script that builds the source and
produces the artifact.
.TP
.B artifact
(Required) Name of the executable produced by the build script.
If omitted, falls back to the value of
.BR name .
.TP
.B last_modified_cmd
(Optional) Custom shell command to retrieve the Last-Modified date of
the remote file. The output must match the HTTP-date format
.RI ( RFC\ 7231 ).
.RE
.PP
If the configuration file does not exist, run
.B pm init
to create a template.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/pm/init.lua
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/pm/cache/
Default build cache directory.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/pm/bin/
Default binary installation directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to derive default paths for configuration, cache, and binary
directories.
